<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Recycling Schedules</h2>
        <p>
            From May to Thanksgiving, residents will receive recycling pickup on guaranteed dates.
            Most households serviced with carts will receive collection every three weeks. Residents serviced with bins will continue to receive once per week collection.

            <h4><b>Guaranteed recycling schedule program:</b></h4>
        <p>1. Carts must be rolled to collection points on designated pickup dates</p>

        <p>2. Carts picked up more frequently than once-per-month program</p>

        <p>3. More frequent collection will increase recycling capacity to accommodate those extra recyclables that used to pile up between pickups</p>

        <p>4. Increased recycling means that we are sending less to landfills, which saves the City money and helps to lower fees and taxes for everyone</p>

            <h4><b>How will I know when my collection dates are?</b></h4>
            Look for collection schedules which will be placed on your recycling cart in the spring, or check the online schedule to look up your next recycling and garbage collection dates.

            <h4><b>Keep Milwaukee Clean & Green.</b></h4>
       
        
